		<title>18         Shale</title>
		<content>   We found a Shale Bing at            
 Bridgend,it                           
 covered a large part of our area so we
 decided to find out about it.         
   At the beginning of the 20th century
 Bridgend supplied Philipstoun with    
 shale.The shale at Bridgend was       
 transported to Philipstoun by train   
 where it was turned into oil.Then the 
 shale was sent back to Bridgend where 
 it was dumped at the Shale Bing.      
   Now the shale is used for making    
 roads and pathways.Some local boys    
 use the Shale Bing for riding         
 bicycles.                             
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
